# Secrets — never commit real credentials. Use .env.example as the template.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Markdown untracked by default; ship WHAT was built, not HOW.
# Product/reference docs are force-kept; add a `!<file>.md` negation for any new
# doc you want committed. The private memory/harness below is never shipped.
*.md
!README.md
!FEEDBACK.md
!INTEGRATION_GUIDE.md
!HACKATHON_CHEATSHEET.md
!dtrc-hackathon.md
!endpoint_wrapper/README.md

# Private development harness & project memory — NEVER commit (reveals "how").
.claude/
docs/
CLAUDE.md

